where ϕ ( Q ) , ϕ ( K ) ∈ R n × d . This strategy effectively reduces the computational complexity to O ( nd 2 ) , rendering it linear with respect to the input length. Linear Transformer [84] is the first work to propose the kernelbased attention. It adopts ϕ ( x ) = elu( x ) + 1 as the kernel function, where elu( · ) denotes the exponential linear unit activation function.
